is the object that we upload in s3 bucket by default is private?

Yes! Objects uploaded to an S3 bucket are private by default.

Who Can Access by Default?
WhoCan Access?Object owner (your AWS account)        ✅ Yes
IAM users in your account (with permissions)         ✅ Yes
Other AWS accounts                                   ❌ No
Public internet / anonymous users                    ❌ No

What's Private by Default When You Create a Bucket?
What                       Default State
Bucket itself              🔒 Private
All objects inside         🔒 Private
Block Public Access        ✅ Enabled (all 4 settings ON)
Bucket ACL                 🔒 Private
Bucket Policy              ❌ None (no public access granted)

