What is versioning in S3?

Versioning means S3 keeps multiple versions of the same object every time you upload, overwrite, or delete it.

Versioning is enabled at Bucket Level only!

Bucket Level — Not Object Level

Versioning setting:
──────────────────
✅ Bucket level    → you enable on entire bucket
❌ Object level    → cannot enable per object

When you enable versioning on bucket:
  ALL objects in that bucket
  get versioning automatically
  you cannot pick specific objects ❌

3 Bucket Versioning States

1. Unversioned (default)
   ──────────────────────
   new bucket
   no versioning
   overwrite = old file gone forever ❌

2. Versioning Enabled
   ───────────────────
   all objects versioned ✅
   every upload = new version
   delete = delete marker added
   can restore anytime ✅

3. Versioning Suspended
   ─────────────────────
   was enabled before
   now suspended
   old versions still exist ✅
   new uploads = no new versions ❌
   cannot go back to unversioned ⚠️

How to Enable in Console

S3 Console
→ Your Bucket
→ Properties tab
→ Bucket Versioning section
→ Edit
→ Enable ✅
→ Save changes

Storage Cost with Versioning
⚠️ Every version is stored separately and you pay for all versions.
file.txt v1 = 10 MB  → you pay for 10 MB
file.txt v2 = 10 MB  → you pay for 20 MB
file.txt v3 = 10 MB  → you pay for 30 MB
To manage costs, use Lifecycle Policies to auto-delete old versions:

S3 Console → Your Bucket → Management tab
Add Lifecycle Rule → expire old versions after X days

How to Restore a Deleted Object

Go to your bucket
Click Show versions toggle (top right)
Find the delete marker on your file
Delete the delete marker → file is restored! ✅

