what is lifecycle management rules in s3?

Lifecycle rules are automatic policies you set on an S3 bucket to automatically transition or expire objects based on their age — saving you storage costs without manual work.

How to Create a Lifecycle Rule

Go to S3 Console → Your Bucket
Click Management tab
Click Create lifecycle rule
Fill in:

Rule name        → give it a name (e.g. "move-logs")
Rule scope       → entire bucket OR specific prefix/tag
Transition       → choose storage class + number of days
Expiration       → choose days to auto delete

Two Types of Lifecycle Actions

Lifecycle Actions
    ├── Transition Actions   (move to cheaper storage class)
    └── Expiration Actions   (automatically delete objects)

1. Transition Actions

automatically move objects to a cheaper storage class after a certain number of days.

Day 0    → S3 Standard         (frequently accessed)
Day 30   → S3 Standard-IA      (less frequently accessed)
Day 90   → S3 Glacier Instant  (rarely accessed)
Day 180  → S3 Glacier Flexible (archive)
Day 365  → S3 Glacier Deep Archive (long-term archive)

2. Expiration Actions
Automatically delete objects after a certain number of days.

Day 0    → Object uploaded
Day 365  → Object automatically deleted ❌

